S2.title: Live Study With Me | 7 hours | Pomodoro 50/10 | Astrophysics PhD Student | rain/lofi | puzzles 2025-06-09 23:22
S2.description:
⬇️⬇️ Links, schedule, and more information down below! ⬇️⬇️

Welcome! Come join for some motivation and accountability! Here we follow the 50/10 Pomodoro method, where we work for 50 minutes and then take a 10 minute break to chat, relax, craft and play puzzles! (we're obsessed with jumble words...)

I am a physics PhD student in my second year at the University of Auckland. I have ADHD so this stream helps to keep me accountable and focused on the tasks I need to get done, so join me for some body-doubling!

My PhD is purely theoretical and computational, so I do lots of coding. My research looks at gravitational wave physics in relation to supermassive black holes and the future Laser Interferometer Space Antenna.

I did my undergraduate and masters in the UK, where I grew up, and then moved to New Zealand for my PhD. I now do purely research and don't take any classes, but I do teach some!

🧑‍🚀 Mission Control Bot Commands 🧑‍🚀
[Note: You can only have one task at a time!]
!add "task" - Add task

Hi all, I'm Endrit, 29 years old (in my 16th year, haha, just a joke!), a medical student studying in lovely Italy.

Welcome to my study stream! Join me as I tackle medical school using the Pomodoro technique. Throughout the stream, you can listen to relaxing background music provided by Lofi Girl, helping you stay focused and in the zone.

Hi friends! Some information for you:     

 - The timer works as follows: 4 sessions of 50 minutes focus (red), 10 minutes short break (light blue). After 3/4 sessions there is a 70 minute long break (dark blue).

- I try to respond to the chat while the timer is blue, but please try to let me study while the timer is red :) You guys are more than welcome to chat with each other though, I love reading the chat during breaks :) 

-- Want to study without music but still want the timer to join on breaks? Or want to turn your video on as well? Join the stream channel in the Discord! The timer is set up there so you never miss a break again! Discord Link down below :)

- Wondering when I'm going to stream next? Study Stream schedule linked below! Click on your time zone to see when I'm going to study next on your time!


About Me:

- I am a 22 yo American dude (Located in Michigan, Eastern Standard Time). I'm born and raised American, my mom was raised in Canada, my dad was raised in America. My grandparents are Pakistani, they moved to the US/Canada like 50 years ago lol.
- I am in my second year of medical school (in the US, you do 4 years of high school, 4 years of university, then 4 years of medical school)
- If you are curious as to how I study, I like to watch lecture videos and take notes on my IPad, and then do Anki (which is a flashcard software on my computer. So if you see me using the remote, I'm doing flashcards!
- If you see me staring out the window, I'm trying to give my eyes a 20 second rest :) (20/20/20 rule) 
- Love y'all, thank you for the support :)            

Remember to like and subscribe to this study stream to stay updated on future study sessions!

Music provided by Lofi Girl

満点学習帳 ( https://www.mantenroom.com ) と連携しています。

くわしくは上記リンクと下の 【コマンドの使い方】 にて。

【コマンドの使い方】

!25 など!で始まる単語をコマンドと言います。コマンドをチャットに書き込むとbot(自動返信ロボット🤖)を通じて学習の記録をつけられます。

!make

あなたの学習記録ページを作成します

学習記録ページはサイト満点学習帳 ( https://www.mantenroom.com )  に作成されます。

!home

あなたの学習記録ページのURLを返します

!25

1回25分の勉強回数(コマ数)を記録します

今日のコマ数と過去全期間の累計コマ数を返します

学習記録ページに反映されます

(!25aと!25bも同じ機能のコマンドです

ほかの人とタイミングがかぶると反応しないので、

かぶりやすいこのコマンドだけ3種類用意してます)

!delete

学習記録ページに関するすべてのデータを削除します😭

そのほか満点学習帳と連携するコマンドの一覧は『学習記録ページ → ? → 目標設定(仮) → ページ最下部』にて見れます。

!room

S29.title: 50대 감정평가사 도전기! 12HR-STUDY WITH ME (스터디 윗미)/공무원 시험/수험생/전문직 시험/혼자 공부/캠스터디/Huntington Beach/채팅은 쉬는시간에~ 2025-06-09 23:22
S29.description:
50대에 접어들게 되면서....
감히 감정평가사라는 정말 어려운 시험에 도전하게 되었습니다.
서울대, 연고대 출신 합격생이 가장 많고, 
8천여명중에 150~200여명 안팎의 인원만 합격하는 극악의 난이도의 시험입니다.
50대는 1년에 보통 전국에서 2~3명 내외로 합격하더군요....
그런 똑똑하고 체력좋은 젊은 20대~30대 친구들한테 제가 무모한 싸움을 걸었네요.
몸과 머리가 젊을때 같지않지만, 절실함 하나만을 가지고 시작했습니다!
유튜브 공부법은 약하디 약한 저의 의지를 바로 잡는데 꼭 필요한 장치인것 같습니다.
매일매일 이해하지 못하고 암기하지 못함에서 오는 
'불합격하면 어떡하지??'라는 극악의 불안감이 엄습해오지만...
꼭 이겨내겠습니다!
올해 4월 1차, 내년 7월 2차 시험 합격을 목표로 달려가고 있습니다.
저를 아시던 모르시던 한번씩 들어오셔서
*구독, 좋아요 눌러주시고*
[공부 잘하고 있는지 확인해 주시고] 
[만약 나약한 모습을 보인다면 쓴소리해주세요] 
부탁드립니다!!
마지막으로, 
여기 들어 오시는 모든 분들이 준비하시는 시험에 꼭 합격하시길 기원드립니다.
감사합니다!!

As I entered my 50s...
I dare to take a very difficult exam called a certified public appraiser.
It's an extremely difficult exam that only about 150~200 out of 8,000 passed every year in Korea.
Usually, only two or three people in their 50s pass the test a year...
I started a reckless fight against those smart, energetic young people in their 20s and 30s.
My body and head aren't like when I was young, but I started with only one desperation!
The YouTube study method seems to be a necessary device to strengthen my weak will.
Everyday i'm worried that I might fail the exam, but I'll overcome it!
I am studying hard with the goal of passing the first test in April this year. 
and the second exam (Final) in July next year.
Whether you know me or not, please come in.
*Please press subscribe and like*
And please check if I am studying well.
If I don't study or show a weak mental state, please say something bitter.
Please!
Lastly, I hope this real-time streaming will be of great help to your studies.
Thank you!!

✧･ﾟ at the beginning of the study sessions, make sure to:
- turn off anything you're not going to be using to study
- have your materials ready to go
- have drinks/food ready so you don't have to get up to go get necessities
- have a clear idea of what you want to accomplish during the session (i.e., choose a task from your to-do list)


✧･ﾟ during the breaks:
- stop working as soon as the timer hits, even if you're mid-sentence
- make sure to get up, do some simple stretches
- refill anything that needs to get refilled
- talk to friends/update family

if you want to continue studying, give yourself a longer break and you can the next session video!

🧉 Hello student, how are you? It's great to have you here!
I just wanted to let you know that this study livestream is live 24 hours a day, every day of the week, so that whenever you feel like studying, you can rely on a platform that motivates you and enables you to achieve that goal. And if you ever feel like appearing on the livestream, join us on this Discord link: [https://discord.gg/K5kcaMSJaU]

💰💸Crowdfunding to buy a camera for the channel (since the cell phone I use as a camera is starting to give problems): https://livepix.gg/vaquinha/comprar-camera

But before we begin, if possible, please leave a like on the video, subscribe to the channel, and share your study objectives in the comments!
Finally, grab your water, matecito, coffee, or tea to stay hydrated during your study sessions.

👾 Discord link: [https://discord.gg/K5kcaMSJaU]
(To join the video call, go to the category "----- 🔴 live stream -----" and then to the channel "🔴-live-🔴")

📅 Schedule for the next livestream: [https://www.canva.com/design/DAE9uFPN...]

🍅 Pomodoro Technique:
We will be using the Pomodoro technique, which consists of four 50-minute study sessions, interspersed with 10-minute breaks. The purpose of this technique is to maintain focus for 50 minutes through conditioning. In the beginning, it might be difficult, so try starting with cycles of 15-25 minutes. However, with persistence, you can achieve the desired results!

⭐ A little bit about me and why I created this channel:
My name is Arthur, I'm 24 years old, and I'm a third-year medical student at UBA College. I created this channel to help myself maintain discipline and focus in my studies, and if possible, to also help other students do the same.

🌙 minimal chatting while the study session is going on.
🌙 be respectful and kind.
🌙 no spamming, advertising and inappropriate behaviour.

Commands:
⭐ !quote - motivational quotes
⭐ !genie - start counting your study time. If u just joined, type !genie. No time will be added yet. When the break starts, type !genie again to add 1 hour. ⭐ !target (task) - to add a task to your to-do list.
⭐ !done (task) - when you finish your task.

S61.description:
Welcome to your auditory sanctuary
In a world filled with noise, chaos, and distractions, our channel is a safe haven for your thoughts. We specialize in creating pure soundscapes—a perfect blend of white noise and gentle instrumental music designed to help you focus, relax, and find peace in your daily life. Whether you're studying, working, meditating, or just relaxing, our carefully crafted music provides the perfect background music for moments of peace and productivity.

The Science Behind Our Soundscapes
Our content is more than just great sounds—it's rooted in scientific principles that promote mental and physical well-being. Here's how our white noise and music works:

White noise helps you focus and relax

White noise contains the same energy across all frequencies, creating a "blanket of sound" that masks distracting noises like traffic, conversation, or household noises.

Research shows that white noise can improve focus by reducing auditory distractions and improving cognitive abilities.

Soothing music for balanced moods

Soft instrumental melodies, such as piano, strings, and ambient pads, stimulate the brain's reward system, releasing dopamine and reducing stress.
These melodies are combined with white noise to create a harmonious atmosphere that promotes relaxation without disrupting your focus.
Brainwave Sync

Our soundscapes are designed to promote alpha brainwaves (8-12 Hz), which are associated with a calm, focused state of mind.
Some tracks also incorporate theta brainwaves (4-7 Hz) to promote creativity and deep relaxation.
What makes us unique?
100% clean sound

No vocals, no lyrics, no distractions—just pure, uninterrupted soundscapes.
Perfect for those who need a clean, soothing listening environment.
Real field recordings

Our white noise tracks contain real-world sounds, such as rain, ocean waves, wind, and forest sounds, recorded in pristine natural environments.
These authentic recordings bring the soothing power of nature directly to your ears.
Crafted to fit every mood

Each track is carefully crafted to meet your specific needs, whether it’s to improve focus, reduce stress, aid sleep, or enhance mindfulness.
Smooth listening experience

We ensured that all tracks have no sudden volume changes or disruptive transitions, providing a smooth and consistent listening experience.
Who is this channel for?
Students and professionals
Boost your productivity with soundscapes that help you focus and stay focused.
Relaxation seekers
Escape the hustle and bustle of daily life and unwind with soothing sounds.
Sleep lovers
Fall into a deep, peaceful sleep with soothing white noise and gentle melodies.
Mindfulness practitioners
Enhance your meditation and yoga practice with sounds that promote inner peace.
Our most popular soundscape
Rainy Day Bliss

The gentle sound of raindrops combined with soft piano sounds. Perfect for studying or relaxing on a cozy afternoon.

Subscribe to our channel and join our growing community of people who value peace, focus, and relaxation. Let us accompany you to create a more focused and balanced life through the power of sound.

無論你是在趕報告、備考，還是想靜靜讀本書，這個空間裡只有書頁翻動聲與輕柔旋律。戴上耳機，讓溫暖的純音樂為你的學習時光注入平靜與動力。這不是一部普通的學習影片，而是一場「陪你讀書」的無聲陪伴，用輕快的節奏帶走壓力，用專注的氛圍點亮你的靈感✨

在綿密的雨聲與輕柔的純音樂交織中，這部影片為你打造一個獨特的沉浸式學習空間。鏡頭前的女孩專注於書頁之間，耳機隔絕外界紛擾。這不僅是一段學習實錄，更是一場心靈的陪伴——無論你是需要專注的學生、熬夜加班的職場人，還是單純渴望片刻安寧的靈魂，這部影片都能成為你書桌旁的「無聲夥伴」。
雨聲作為天然的白噪音，已被科學證實能提升大腦的專注力（參考學習心理學研究）。影片中刻意保留環境音的細膩層次——雨滴輕敲窗沿、營造出「隔絕卻不孤單」的空間感。搭配原創的輕音樂，以鋼琴與弦樂為主調，節奏緩慢而穩定，避免過度起伏干擾思緒，卻又在副歌段落加入少量木管樂器的跳躍音階，暗示「學習中偶爾的小確幸」

想象一下：深夜，窗外细雨淅沥，你坐在温暖的灯光下，戴上耳机，沉浸在学习的世界里。这份宁静与专注，正是我们为你精心打造的学习伴侣。
